					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This tale didn't grip me too much, but I like how it fleshed out (heh) the Buddhist/mindfulness themes hinted at in the SCP. I also like, as psul noted, the irony of the protagonist getting attached to unattachment.</p> <p>(I also enjoyed seeing the very real example of mindfulness and Buddhist philosophy used in addiction recovery, which a lot of people have no clue exists! &#8230;even though our protagonist may have missed the point here)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
